This page is the wiki for the Coursera course Drugs and the Brain.  
  
**Course Syllabus**   
  
Week 1. Introductory concepts. Drugs, drug receptors, neuroscience. Resting potentials. Equivalent circuits.  
[[Drugsandbrain:Transcripts 1 | Edited Transcripts]]  
[[Drugsandbrain:Lecture Notes 1 | Lecture Notes]]    
[[Drugsandbrain:References 1 | References]]     
  
Week 2. Drugs open and block ion channels. Dose-response relations. Desensitization. Epilepsy drugs. Drugs activate and block G protein pathways.  
[[Drugsandbrain:Transcripts 2 | Edited Transcripts]]  
[[Drugsandbrain:Lecture Notes 2 | Lecture Notes]]  
[[Drugsandbrain:References 2 | References]]  
[[Drugsandbrain:Background 2 | Other Background material]]    

Week 3. Drugs block neurotransmitter transporters. Recreational drugs. Nicotine Addiction.  
[[Drugsandbrain:Transcripts 3 | Edited Transcripts]]  
[[Drugsandbrain:Lecture Notes 3 | Lecture Notes]]    
[[Drugsandbrain:References 3 | References]]    
  
Week 4. Drugs for neurodegenerative and psychiatric diseases.  
[[Drugsandbrain:Transcripts 4 | Edited Transcripts]]  
[[Drugsandbrain:Lecture Notes 4 | Lecture Notes]]    
[[Drugsandbrain:References 4 | References]]  
[[Drugsandbrain:Background 4 | Other Background material]]      
  
Week 5. Drugs for psychiatric diseases. Developing new drugs. Inside-out drug action. Interventional neuroscience.  
